SIMPLE: overflow
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overflow
<hw>O`ver*flow"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overflowed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overflowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>oferfl<?/wan</ets>. See <er>Over</er>, and <er>Flow</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To flow over; to cover with, or as with, water or other
fluid; to spread over; to inundate; to overwhelm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The northern nations <qex>overflowed</qex> all Christendom.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To flow over the brim of; to fill more than
full.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overflow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overflow
<hw>O`ver*flow"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To run over the
bounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be superabundant; to abound.</def>
<rj><au>Rogers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overflow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Overflow
<hw>O"ver*flow`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
flowing over, as of water or other fluid; an inundation.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which flows over; a superfluous portion; a
superabundance.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An outlet for the escape of surplus
liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Overflow meeting</b></col>, <cd>a meeting constituted of
the surplus or overflow of another audience.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overflowing</ent>⟦br⟧
